-[Aki] Two, three, four.
-Two, three, four.

22:43.320 --> 22:46.198
[Suzuki] Two, and three, and four.
Aki, keep counting.

22:46.782 --> 22:49.409
-[Aki] Two, three, four.
-Three, four.

22:50.452 --> 22:52.954
-[Aki] Two, three, four.
-[Suzuki snaps fingers]

22:53.705 --> 22:55.290
[Aki] Two, three, four.

22:55.374 --> 22:57.417
If the waltz is an elegant courtship…

22:57.501 --> 22:59.586
[Aki] Two, three, four.

22:59.669 --> 23:01.505
…then Latin dance is raw eroticism.

23:01.588 --> 23:03.090
[Aki] …three, four.

23:03.173 --> 23:05.050
[intriguing ethereal music playing]

23:06.635 --> 23:08.261
Arouse them, seduce them.

23:08.345 --> 23:10.305
Don't stop till you make 'em wet.

23:10.389 --> 23:12.391
-[laughs]
-[Aki] Two, three, four.

23:12.474 --> 23:13.725
You're not sexy, guy.

23:13.809 --> 23:16.311
-[Aki] Two, three, four.
-Four.

23:16.895 --> 23:19.689
Two, and three, and four.

23:19.773 --> 23:22.275
[Sugiki] One, two, three.

23:22.359 --> 23:24.778
One, two, three.

23:24.861 --> 23:26.905
One, two, three.

23:26.988 --> 23:30.659
[Aki] Sorry. Suzuki can be
a little rough around the edges.

23:30.742 --> 23:31.827
[Fusako] Don't worry.

23:32.577 --> 23:34.121
So you two together?

23:34.830 --> 23:36.039
[Aki chuckles]

23:36.748 --> 23:39.709
Well, there was something there
at one point, I guess.

23:40.210 --> 23:43.338
But now, I just want to go further
as dance partners.

23:46.675 --> 23:48.760
How about you and Mr. Sugiki?

23:49.261 --> 23:50.846
There's love in your dancing.

23:52.431 --> 23:56.393
Mr. Sugiki took me as a partner
when I was nothing.

23:56.476 --> 23:58.228
He's brought me so far.

23:59.771 --> 24:01.940
I trust him with everything

24:02.566 --> 24:04.526
and just follow his lead.

24:06.778 --> 24:09.698
I've never felt loved by him at all,

24:10.657 --> 24:12.576
and I don't think I need to.

24:26.715 --> 24:28.383
[music fades]

24:29.050 --> 24:31.636
[Sugiki] We still have some time
before the first train.

24:32.262 --> 24:33.972
You can rest a little longer.

24:38.268 --> 24:40.061
Do you do this every day?

24:48.320 --> 24:49.988
I can't stand it.

24:52.199 --> 24:53.992
I won't be second again.

24:56.244 --> 24:57.996
[Sugiki exhales]

25:00.373 --> 25:04.669
I'm not the type to try to make
an audience boo judges' decisions.

25:05.795 --> 25:07.214
[sighs]

25:09.966 --> 25:11.259
I recall

25:11.760 --> 25:14.262
you said you liked being number one,
didn't you?

25:16.097 --> 25:18.892
I also like being at the top of the pack.

25:20.810 --> 25:24.731
-I'm only at the top of my turf, right?
-[Sugiki] Are you going to go all in?

25:26.775 --> 25:28.193
Doesn't it look like it?

25:31.696 --> 25:33.698
[Sugiki sighs]

25:36.284 --> 25:38.286
You be the judge of that.

25:44.834 --> 25:46.002
[groans]

25:47.128 --> 25:48.255
[sighs]

26:02.936 --> 26:04.938
["Bandolera" playing]

26:30.589 --> 26:33.550
[Suzuki] God, it felt like the wind
had gone right through me.

26:35.552 --> 26:37.095
It stirred my soul.

26:37.637 --> 26:38.888
It felt like

26:39.931 --> 26:41.975
that hot wind of Havana.

26:47.188 --> 26:49.190
["Bandolera" continues]

26:56.615 --> 26:58.950
My soul is still in Havana.

27:00.994 --> 27:05.081
It's the kingdom of sun, music, and dance.

27:06.124 --> 27:08.126
[plane engine roars]

27:15.884 --> 27:17.510
[music fades]

27:17.594 --> 27:20.639
[Suzuki] Doesn't matter how small
the world may be,

27:20.722 --> 27:23.183
I sure as hell can't see Havana from here.

27:23.266 --> 27:24.225
…four.

27:24.809 --> 27:27.812
-[Suzuki] Two, three, four.
-[Aki] Two, three, four.

27:27.896 --> 27:30.398
-[Suzuki] Two, and three, and four.
-[Aki] Two, three, four.

27:30.482 --> 27:32.734
[Sugiki] One, two, three.

27:33.318 --> 27:35.111
One, two, three.

27:35.195 --> 27:37.697
-[Fusako] Face right.
-[Sugiki] One, two, three.

27:37.781 --> 27:39.491
One, full count.

27:39.574 --> 27:42.118
One, two, three.

27:42.202 --> 27:44.746
One, two, three.

27:44.829 --> 27:45.830
One.

27:46.915 --> 27:48.416
Okay, one more time.

27:50.543 --> 27:51.628
[exhales]

27:56.257 --> 27:57.550
[Suzuki] Just a minute.

27:57.634 --> 28:00.595
-Can I put some music on?
-[Sugiki] You're not ready.

28:00.679 --> 28:03.223
-Let me put some music.
-I said no, you're not ready for it yet.

28:03.306 --> 28:05.684
-[keyboard clacking]
-This thing's not even working.

28:05.767 --> 28:08.103
My method is to drill the counts
into your body,

28:08.186 --> 28:10.689
without even the slightest distraction.

28:10.772 --> 28:13.108
-[Suzuki] God, I want music.
-Okay, let's go.

28:13.191 --> 28:14.693
-[Fusako] All right.
-[Suzuki sighs]

28:14.776 --> 28:16.319
[Sugiki] Two, three.

28:16.403 --> 28:18.738
One, two, three.

28:18.822 --> 28:20.740
One, two, and three.

28:20.824 --> 28:23.451
One, two, three.

28:23.535 --> 28:25.620
One, two, three.

28:25.704 --> 28:26.830
[clears throat]

28:28.206 --> 28:29.207
[Suzuki] What?

28:30.458 --> 28:32.669
Your lead is uncomfortable.

28:32.752 --> 28:34.295
-Your holds are self-centered…
-Hold on.

28:34.379 --> 28:35.422
-…and unreliable.
-Hey.

28:35.505 --> 28:38.925
-Quit complaining. Move the way I steer.
-If I give in, I feel like I'm in danger.

28:47.308 --> 28:48.435
What is it?

28:49.894 --> 28:52.021
You're waltzing like you're a servant.

29:00.530 --> 29:01.698
What does that mean?

29:04.909 --> 29:07.537
The waltz is danced
by ladies and gentlemen.

29:08.455 --> 29:11.750
It looks very elegant,
but it's also relentless.

29:13.793 --> 29:18.006
The woman must dance in those high heels,
twisting her waist for hours on end.

29:19.048 --> 29:22.385
The pain is pure torture.

29:26.473 --> 29:27.932
And in such a state,

29:28.016 --> 29:31.186
she will not yield
to a rough and vulgar man.

29:44.616 --> 29:47.118
-What the hell?
-You should try being the woman for once.

29:48.036 --> 29:49.954
Lower your shoulder blades
and turn out your arms.

29:50.038 --> 29:51.790
That part is the same as the man's.

29:51.873 --> 29:55.126
Now, keep your hips there,
but rotate only your chest to the left.

29:55.210 --> 29:56.961
Your shoulders to the right.

29:57.045 --> 30:00.215
Stretch your neck.
Stretch it away from your right.

30:00.298 --> 30:02.217
Up to the left. That's it.

30:04.719 --> 30:07.138
Now, get up on your toes.

30:11.643 --> 30:13.061
-[Suzuki grunts]
-Higher.

30:14.854 --> 30:17.273
Hold it right there. Stay.

30:21.945 --> 30:23.071
[grunts]

30:25.240 --> 30:26.282
[grunts]

30:28.743 --> 30:30.578
Your stance is beautiful.

30:35.416 --> 30:37.877
Without me,
just standing is hard, isn't it?

30:41.714 --> 30:45.510
During hardship, the gentleman
offers his hand to support his partner.

30:45.593 --> 30:48.179
That's how it works in ballroom dance.

31:04.821 --> 31:06.865
"Move the way I steer you," right?

31:07.907 --> 31:09.158
[groans]

31:16.541 --> 31:18.251
[Sugiki] Natural turn.

31:19.502 --> 31:22.505
Running spin turn.

31:22.589 --> 31:24.340
Chassé roll.

31:24.424 --> 31:26.551
["The Blue Danube,
Waltz Opus 314" playing]

31:26.634 --> 31:28.303
[Sugiki] Left whisk.

31:31.681 --> 31:33.558
Standing spin.

31:40.106 --> 31:44.068
Syncopated running finish.

31:44.152 --> 31:46.154
[music intensifies]

31:54.495 --> 31:56.247
Throwaway.

31:57.248 --> 31:59.584
Oversway.

32:08.134 --> 32:09.302
How was that?

32:10.011 --> 32:11.888
Did you feel like a princess?

32:40.667 --> 32:42.418
[music ends]

32:42.502 --> 32:44.170
[footsteps approaching]

32:48.591 --> 32:50.551
[Sugiki] Let's go get something to eat.

32:59.018 --> 33:01.020
[gentle orchestral music playing]

33:02.271 --> 33:03.231
[Suzuki] Hmm?

33:04.649 --> 33:05.650
What's that?

33:08.444 --> 33:10.446
-Thank you.
-This is coronation chicken.

33:10.530 --> 33:14.158
Served at Queen Elizabeth's coronation
in 1953.

33:16.452 --> 33:17.453
[sniffles]

33:19.372 --> 33:20.206
Mmm.

33:20.999 --> 33:22.625
The apricots you just tasted

33:22.709 --> 33:26.170
were arranged
to resemble scattered jewels.

33:26.254 --> 33:28.965
Britain was victorious,
but they were still rationing at the time,

33:29.048 --> 33:31.968
and this dish astonished guests
from around the world.

33:45.565 --> 33:48.109
Elbows off the table.
That's how a dog eats.

33:48.192 --> 33:50.278
I'm eating like this 'cause it's good.

33:51.404 --> 33:52.613
You get it, right?

33:53.406 --> 33:54.323
It's good.

33:54.824 --> 33:55.867
Tastes like curry.

34:01.289 --> 34:03.249
More wine. Mm.

34:06.878 --> 34:09.255
You shouldn't hold the glass
while it's being poured.

34:10.048 --> 34:11.049
[scoffs]

34:11.924 --> 34:14.135
When you're at a banquet,
you don't hold it by the bowl

34:14.218 --> 34:15.970
but lower on the stem, like this.

34:16.054 --> 34:17.055
I got it.

34:17.555 --> 34:18.681
-[chuckles]
-Hmm?

34:18.765 --> 34:22.018
What does any of this
have to do with ballroom dancing?

34:24.395 --> 34:25.813
I know how to eat, man.

34:36.324 --> 34:38.076
Imagine this scenario.

34:38.868 --> 34:43.956
You manage to beat every other 10 dancer
and rise to the top of the world.

34:46.292 --> 34:47.585
After your honor dance,

34:47.668 --> 34:51.047
you get an invitation
from someone who loved your performance.

34:51.631 --> 34:53.966
This is not a wrap party
at a dance school.

34:55.718 --> 34:58.721
Big-time sponsors and patrons
the envy of all dancers

34:58.805 --> 35:00.431
will be waiting for you.

35:04.018 --> 35:06.187
[sniffles] I get it now.

35:07.647 --> 35:09.816
So this is another lesson for me?

35:13.402 --> 35:14.779
Okay, guy.

35:17.865 --> 35:19.408
[phone keypad beeping]

35:20.868 --> 35:22.453
I have a lesson for you.

35:22.537 --> 35:24.914
["Son de la Loma"
by Trio Congri Cubano playing]

35:31.796 --> 35:33.798
[people cheering]

35:57.989 --> 35:59.949
So, you like it?

36:00.032 --> 36:01.159
[Sugiki] Yes.

36:01.242 --> 36:03.119
[Suzuki] It's the real taste of Cuba.

36:10.585 --> 36:11.502
Drink.

36:12.545 --> 36:13.796
Come on, drink!

36:15.173 --> 36:16.257
Break!

36:16.340 --> 36:17.675
Take a break!

36:18.718 --> 36:20.136
He's boring!

36:20.887 --> 36:22.597
[people booing]

36:24.056 --> 36:27.059
-Let's get him drinking!
-So you're the "Emperor," huh?

36:27.143 --> 36:29.187
It's fantastic!

36:29.270 --> 36:31.022
-[man] Salud!
-Salud!

36:31.105 --> 36:32.899
Salud!

36:33.774 --> 36:35.234
-[Suzuki] Salud.
-Salud.

36:39.655 --> 36:41.073
Hey, Sugiki, let's go!

36:41.157 --> 36:42.366
-Huh?
-Come on!

36:43.201 --> 36:44.702
-Smile!
-What?

36:44.785 --> 36:46.329
Just smile, man!

36:46.412 --> 36:47.997
Fake it if you have to!

36:48.080 --> 36:49.373
Just smile!

36:49.457 --> 36:52.001
Come on! Come on! Come on!
Come on! Come on! Come on!

36:52.084 --> 36:54.086
[cheers of encouragement]

36:56.631 --> 36:58.382
[laughing]

36:58.466 --> 37:00.259
Don't think about it! Don't…

37:00.343 --> 37:02.428
Don't count with this. Make some noise!

37:03.012 --> 37:05.890
Latin is about
making your body the instrument.

37:09.185 --> 37:11.187
[gentle piano music playing]

37:21.030 --> 37:23.991
[Suzuki] At around the same time
Queen Elizabeth II

37:24.075 --> 37:25.993
was serving coronation chicken,

37:27.453 --> 37:30.456
Castro was starting his revolution
in Cuba.

37:33.626 --> 37:37.255
That's probably how big
the difference was between us as well.

37:41.509 --> 37:43.719
SUZUKI DANCE SCHOOL

37:43.803 --> 37:45.471
[Suzuki] It's almost like a wave…

37:45.554 --> 37:47.223
[gentle piano music continues]

37:47.306 --> 37:49.100
…right through his fingertips.

37:51.102 --> 37:52.895
While holding his hand, I can…

37:53.437 --> 37:55.273
I feel his emotions, you know?

37:56.232 --> 37:57.233
You get it?

38:00.194 --> 38:01.737
Like superiority.

38:03.281 --> 38:04.615
Possessiveness.

38:05.408 --> 38:07.034
The urge to control.

38:08.703 --> 38:11.205
And sometimes I can feel gentleness.

38:11.831 --> 38:13.124
Expectation.

38:15.459 --> 38:17.753
I don't even know how
to explain it properly.

38:17.837 --> 38:20.631
I mean, it's like
I can feel everything he's feeling.

38:20.715 --> 38:21.966
You know? [chuckles]

38:23.259 --> 38:25.177
You sound like you're in love.

38:25.261 --> 38:26.387
Huh?

38:28.055 --> 38:29.307
Don't be stupid.

38:31.017 --> 38:32.435
-[chuckles]
-[phone ringing]

38:33.477 --> 38:35.313
-[Suzuki grunts]
-[phone ringing]

38:40.318 --> 38:41.694
-[Suzuki] Look.
-Hmm?

38:43.279 --> 38:44.989
Sugiki. [chuckles]

38:46.657 --> 38:48.826
-[people cheering]
-[Suzuki] Hey, what's up?

38:51.245 --> 38:52.288
Are you there?

38:54.540 --> 38:56.584
You there? Can't hear you.

38:57.084 --> 39:00.671
[emcee] This is
the UK's Best Dance Championships…

39:00.755 --> 39:01.589
The UK's Best?

39:01.672 --> 39:04.175
…Professional Latin semifinal.

39:05.009 --> 39:06.177
The paso doble.

39:06.260 --> 39:07.470
You're in the UK?

39:08.387 --> 39:10.890
[Sugiki] Didn't I tell you?
That night we went out,

39:10.973 --> 39:13.517
I thought I mentioned
I was leaving the next day.

39:14.435 --> 39:16.228
-No, you didn't.
-All right.

39:17.104 --> 39:19.815
It's a competition I enter every year.
You must've known.

39:19.899 --> 39:21.192
That's not the point.

39:21.275 --> 39:23.486
["España Cañí" playing]

39:23.569 --> 39:25.321
I'm next. Gotta go.

39:25.404 --> 39:27.948
Wait, hold on. Hold on.

39:28.032 --> 39:28.949
Yes?

39:31.160 --> 39:32.453
Just come back soon.

39:35.414 --> 39:37.416
-[music continues]
-[crowd clapping]

39:43.005 --> 39:44.548
[disconnect tone]

39:44.632 --> 39:45.883
[sighs]

39:54.392 --> 39:55.518
[phone thuds]

39:57.436 --> 39:58.604
[Aki] What did he say?

39:58.687 --> 40:01.899
This year's Open,
we're gonna move up two in the rankings.

40:01.982 --> 40:02.858
Huh?

40:02.942 --> 40:04.944
And keep the All-Japan Champion title.

40:05.027 --> 40:06.529
[pensive music playing]

40:06.612 --> 40:07.446
Then…

40:10.699 --> 40:11.909
in 10 Dance…

40:14.078 --> 40:15.579
we'll beat Sugiki.

40:16.247 --> 40:17.998
[emcee] Ladies and gentlemen,

40:18.082 --> 40:21.794
we now come to
the Professional Ballroom semifinal.

40:21.877 --> 40:24.588
Twelve couples have been recalled.

40:24.672 --> 40:27.049
Please welcome them to the floor.

40:27.133 --> 40:29.135
[cheering, clapping]

40:44.066 --> 40:46.777
[emcee] All present and correct.

40:47.278 --> 40:50.823
Your first dance, the slow waltz.

40:51.323 --> 40:53.325
[slow waltz music playing]

40:59.582 --> 41:01.584
[indistinct chattering]

41:06.589 --> 41:08.215
There's Ms. Martha.

41:08.799 --> 41:11.802
[man 2] She's the president of the WDL,
isn't she?

41:11.886 --> 41:14.847
[man 1] She's a mentor devoted
to fostering Asian dancers.

41:15.347 --> 41:16.724
Sugiki's her prize student.

41:16.807 --> 41:19.685
He's indispensable
in their Asian market strategy.

41:20.811 --> 41:23.481
I thought they were extraordinary.
They seem to be flourishing,

41:23.564 --> 41:25.858
although I wonder…
perhaps a different combination.

41:25.941 --> 41:27.943
[classical music playing]

41:30.905 --> 41:33.240
[Martha] What is
with that ridiculously exaggerated hold

41:33.324 --> 41:35.117
you seem to insist on doing?

41:35.951 --> 41:37.995
All you are doing
is placing a strain on Fusako.

41:38.078 --> 41:40.706
There is absolutely no unity
in your dancing.

41:41.874 --> 41:43.083
[Sugiki sighs]

41:44.418 --> 41:47.505
It's best to retire
at the height of your glory.

41:49.590 --> 41:51.258
Have you ever imagined
what it would be like

41:51.342 --> 41:52.927
when the audience grows tired of you?

41:53.010 --> 41:54.178
Martha.

41:55.888 --> 42:00.851
Alberto Boemer has been crowned
World Latin Champion 11 years in a row.

42:04.146 --> 42:06.357
I haven't even been champion once.

42:06.440 --> 42:10.569
[Martha] Dance is neither
about technique nor stamina.

42:11.237 --> 42:14.323
Love is what makes it whole, but

42:15.866 --> 42:18.494
I don't feel any love
in the way you dance.

42:23.374 --> 42:24.375
[Martha] Hm.

42:31.340 --> 42:34.051
[Sugiki] Watch your frame.
Make the adjustment.

42:34.134 --> 42:35.386
[Fusako] Yes, beautiful.

42:35.469 --> 42:36.428
[Sugiki] That's it.

42:37.012 --> 42:38.472
[Fusako] Very nice.

42:38.556 --> 42:40.808
Stretch your arms even more.

42:41.850 --> 42:44.186
Yes, very nice.

42:44.270 --> 42:46.689
[Sugiki] Yes, that's good.
Good work today.

42:46.772 --> 42:48.607
-[man] Thank you.
-[woman] Thank you.

42:48.691 --> 42:50.150
When did you get back?

42:50.234 --> 42:52.486
-Thank you for coming.
-See you next time.

42:52.570 --> 42:53.487
Thank you.

43:04.123 --> 43:06.083
[Sugiki] Let's try it with music today.

43:16.093 --> 43:18.470
["River Flows in You" playing]

43:21.390 --> 43:24.768
Two, three. One, two, three.

43:24.852 --> 43:27.146
One, two, three.

43:27.229 --> 43:29.023
One, two, three.

43:29.106 --> 43:31.483
One, two, three.

43:31.567 --> 43:33.694
One, two, three.

43:33.777 --> 43:35.821
One, two, three.

43:35.904 --> 43:37.781
One, two, three.

43:37.865 --> 43:39.992
Careful. Two, three.

43:40.075 --> 43:42.286
One, full count.

43:42.870 --> 43:45.372
Two, three. One.

44:35.172 --> 44:37.174
[music intensifies]

45:07.329 --> 45:09.748
-[Suzuki] Can I ask you something?
-[Sugiki] Hmm?

45:09.832 --> 45:12.084
[Suzuki] Did you grow up
in Martha Milton's house?

45:14.878 --> 45:15.879
[Suzuki] Yes.

45:16.880 --> 45:20.426
[sniffles] My mother was
with me, too, at first.

45:20.509 --> 45:21.844
[music fades]

45:21.927 --> 45:24.012
It felt like I had two mothers.

45:27.141 --> 45:28.350
One day,

45:29.101 --> 45:31.645
Martha took me to the Blackpool Tower.

45:33.063 --> 45:35.232
I saw a large framed photograph there.

45:38.944 --> 45:42.531
Martha and a man
who was as dour as the Grim Reaper.

45:42.614 --> 45:45.826
They looked like
they were ascending into the heavens.

45:45.909 --> 45:47.911
[poignant piano music playing]

45:53.250 --> 45:55.252
[Martha] Do you want to dance like this?

45:56.962 --> 45:58.005
Then,

45:59.173 --> 46:00.382
Shinya,

46:02.217 --> 46:03.719
become a man.

46:04.595 --> 46:08.223
Become the kind of man admired by all.

46:10.142 --> 46:12.144
The finest gentleman.

46:16.607 --> 46:18.609
[poignant piano music continues]

46:19.568 --> 46:22.488
[Suzuki] So you admired him
and wanted to be just like him?

46:23.989 --> 46:24.948
[Sugiki] No.

46:26.408 --> 46:31.079
I think I wanted to take his place,
to be beautiful and terrifying.

46:31.997 --> 46:33.499
[music fades]

46:33.582 --> 46:35.709
Until I was consumed by fear.

46:37.711 --> 46:39.338
[melodic string music playing]

46:45.093 --> 46:47.471
Cuba, what's it really like?

46:47.971 --> 46:49.890
-[Suzuki] Cuba?
-Yes.

46:50.766 --> 46:52.434
It's music.

46:53.143 --> 46:54.102
Dance.

46:54.603 --> 46:55.437
Love.

46:57.773 --> 46:59.399
Romance and the sea.

47:02.694 --> 47:06.323
Cubans fall in love so easily.
Then they marry.

47:07.157 --> 47:08.992
My mom was like that.

47:09.785 --> 47:12.538
Every time we moved to a new place,
it happened.

47:26.426 --> 47:28.136
[tender piano music playing]

47:28.220 --> 47:30.097
Is the sky blue?

47:31.098 --> 47:32.474
[Suzuki chuckles]

47:33.267 --> 47:34.518
[laughs]

47:35.269 --> 47:36.603
It's so blue.

47:37.813 --> 47:40.649
The beaches are always empty,
so when you fall in love,

47:40.732 --> 47:41.984
you go to the beach.

47:43.026 --> 47:44.027
[music fades]

47:44.111 --> 47:45.737
No one disturbs you there.

47:47.072 --> 47:49.491
It's just the two of you
under the palm trees.

47:53.203 --> 47:54.329
[chuckles]

47:56.039 --> 47:57.082
Hm.

47:59.293 --> 48:00.752
[exhales]

48:02.212 --> 48:05.090
["Besame Mucho" by Ballroom Orchestra
and singers playing]

48:13.432 --> 48:15.559
[in Spanish] ♪ Kiss me ♪

48:17.853 --> 48:20.814
♪ Kiss me deeply ♪

48:24.526 --> 48:28.196
♪ As if tonight were ♪

48:28.280 --> 48:32.576
♪ Our very last ♪

48:36.288 --> 48:39.750
♪ Kiss me ♪

48:39.833 --> 48:42.878
♪ Kiss me deeply ♪

48:46.798 --> 48:50.594
♪ For I'm afraid I might lose you ♪

48:50.677 --> 48:54.598
♪ Once it's passed ♪

48:58.310 --> 49:00.812
♪ Kiss me ♪

49:02.439 --> 49:06.193
♪ Kiss me deeply ♪

49:09.154 --> 49:12.908
♪ As if tonight were ♪

49:12.991 --> 49:17.204
♪ Our very last ♪

49:20.540 --> 49:23.919
♪ Kiss me ♪

49:24.503 --> 49:27.965
♪ Kiss me deeply ♪

49:31.468 --> 49:35.263
♪ For I'm afraid I might lose you ♪

49:35.347 --> 49:39.351
♪ Once it's passed… ♪

49:46.233 --> 49:49.277
-["Tango Brujo" playing]
-[in English] Slow, slow.

49:49.361 --> 49:50.445
Quick, quick.

49:50.988 --> 49:52.072
Hold it there.

49:52.990 --> 49:53.824
Breathe in.

49:53.907 --> 49:55.534
-[Sugiki] Right here.
-Okay.

49:55.617 --> 49:56.702
[Sugiki] Like that.

49:56.785 --> 49:57.703
[Fusako] Quick.

49:58.787 --> 49:59.788
[Sugiki] That's it.

50:00.372 --> 50:02.666
I just need a drink of water. Sorry.

50:04.001 --> 50:05.002
[Sugiki] That's it.

50:06.628 --> 50:07.879
Very good.

50:09.381 --> 50:10.632
A little more open.

50:12.509 --> 50:13.510
That's it.

50:14.386 --> 50:15.220
Very good.

50:15.303 --> 50:19.558
You know, Shinya's been crazy
about Mr. Sugiki for a while too.

50:19.641 --> 50:20.642
Yeah?

50:21.643 --> 50:24.980
[Aki] A few years ago,
he happened to see a video.

50:26.565 --> 50:28.942
He said, "He's the perfect dancer."

50:30.152 --> 50:33.155
But then he said, "It looks
like he's in pain," which is weird.

50:33.238 --> 50:35.198
[Sugiki] Keep going like that. Okay.

50:35.282 --> 50:36.450
Quick, quick.

50:37.617 --> 50:39.453
Use your leg for support.

50:39.953 --> 50:43.582
I think you wore a black dress?
You were dancing the tango, right?

50:45.751 --> 50:49.171
I don't think that was me.

50:50.255 --> 50:51.381
-[Sugiki] Quick, quick.
-Huh?

50:52.007 --> 50:55.385
I've never worn
a black dress in a competition.

50:55.469 --> 50:56.845
[Sugiki] And again.

50:58.472 --> 50:59.890
Shall we continue?

51:00.515 --> 51:01.391
Hm.

51:03.018 --> 51:04.311
[Sugiki] Support it.

51:04.394 --> 51:07.439
Wide, wide. Quick, quick.

51:07.522 --> 51:09.441
-[El Tango Gordo" playing]
-Walk, walk.

51:10.942 --> 51:12.110
Position.

51:14.237 --> 51:15.489
Neck.

51:16.156 --> 51:17.157
Quick.

51:18.200 --> 51:20.660
Don't rush. Don't rush. Don't rush.

51:29.086 --> 51:30.087
Slow.

51:31.588 --> 51:33.757
Frame, frame. Keep your frame.

51:33.840 --> 51:35.008
Don't break it.

51:40.222 --> 51:42.099
Rotation. Rotation.

51:42.182 --> 51:45.435
Together. Do it together.
Don't try to dance on your own!

51:46.269 --> 51:48.105
[Sugiki huffs, tuts]

51:54.694 --> 51:55.737
Take a break.

51:58.740 --> 52:01.284
-Aki, why don't you get some water?
-Okay.

52:05.080 --> 52:06.331
[music stops abruptly]

52:07.207 --> 52:08.542
[door opens]

52:08.625 --> 52:10.836
[Suzuki breathes heavily]

52:10.919 --> 52:11.920
[door closes]

52:12.003 --> 52:14.005
[breathing heavily]

52:19.678 --> 52:21.429
What's different between our leads?

52:23.056 --> 52:25.475
[Aki] Mm… well…

52:27.310 --> 52:29.479
With Mr. Sugiki,

52:30.397 --> 52:32.732
I know exactly where I should be.

52:33.316 --> 52:36.611
No matter what the movement is,
it never varies.

52:37.946 --> 52:42.868
And… the balance
between force and gentleness,

52:42.951 --> 52:45.245
it makes my body want to follow his lead.

52:46.413 --> 52:48.957
And, then, with you,

52:49.916 --> 52:52.836
it's more like,
"I'm having fun, so you must be, too."

52:52.919 --> 52:54.921
[ethereal pensive music playing]

52:59.843 --> 53:03.013
Sometimes that works for me,
and sometimes it doesn't.

53:03.513 --> 53:04.389
Hmm?

53:06.433 --> 53:07.392
[sighs]

53:07.475 --> 53:12.022
Fusako said that when she and Mr. Sugiki
entered their first competition,

53:12.105 --> 53:13.440
he said to her…

53:15.942 --> 53:17.277
[both] "Ms. Yagami."

53:18.111 --> 53:20.197
-[Aki] "Now that you're…"
-Now that you're my partner…

53:20.280 --> 53:23.575
I will make you dance
more beautifully than anyone.

53:25.952 --> 53:27.954
Every dancer in the world will say,

53:28.455 --> 53:30.790
"Fusako Yagami is beautiful."

53:30.874 --> 53:33.001
"I want to be Fusako Yagami."

53:35.170 --> 53:38.590
That will be my ultimate joy.

53:49.976 --> 53:51.519
Jeez.

53:52.145 --> 53:54.439
I wish someone would say that to me.

53:54.522 --> 53:58.610
You know, have that kind of caring?

53:58.693 --> 54:00.237
-You don't have it.
-Caring?

54:00.320 --> 54:01.613
-Caring.
-No way.

54:01.696 --> 54:04.532
-You should try it sometime.
-It's sentimental crap.

54:05.742 --> 54:06.952
[Aki chuckles]

54:10.247 --> 54:11.498
-Oh, hey. By the way…
-[sighs]

54:11.581 --> 54:14.125
…that video you sent over to me
the other day?

54:14.209 --> 54:15.418
-Yeah?
-[door opens]

54:15.502 --> 54:17.337
That wasn't Fusako dancing.

54:18.880 --> 54:19.923
[door closes]

54:20.465 --> 54:21.383
You sure?

54:21.466 --> 54:23.927
She told me
she never wore black while competing.

54:27.138 --> 54:28.974
Or something like that.

54:31.559 --> 54:32.727
[sighs]

54:38.608 --> 54:40.610
["Nadie Sabe" playing]

54:45.699 --> 54:48.576
[man] Havana salad and a… beer?

54:59.713 --> 55:02.090
[indistinct chattering]

55:02.173 --> 55:03.842
-Hey!
-[Suzuki] Hey.

55:07.929 --> 55:09.389
I don't know what's going on.

55:10.890 --> 55:12.434
I can't dance anymore.

55:16.354 --> 55:17.981
He's the one in control.

55:18.857 --> 55:21.985
I thought I was the one using him, but

55:23.486 --> 55:25.071
I'm the one being used.

55:27.866 --> 55:31.036
Keeps throwing me off my game
and keeping me on edge.

55:32.537 --> 55:34.331
I mean, what am I to him?

55:37.584 --> 55:38.752
Sounds like love.

55:40.045 --> 55:43.048
-[both laugh]
-What are you talking about?

55:45.925 --> 55:47.302
Do you want him?

55:49.471 --> 55:51.097
[both laughing]

55:52.640 --> 55:54.017
Seriously, do you?

55:55.018 --> 55:57.312
Guys can be attracted
to other guys, right?

55:57.395 --> 55:59.731
Ah, come on!

56:01.441 --> 56:04.110
[bartender 1] If you're cool
with someone else stealing him, back off.

56:04.194 --> 56:05.695
Let someone else take a shot.

56:05.779 --> 56:07.864
[laughing]

56:16.122 --> 56:19.250
[singer, in Spanish] ♪ Love me
And kiss me ♪

56:19.334 --> 56:21.711
♪ If not, forget about me ♪

56:21.795 --> 56:24.923
♪ No one knows what the future holds ♪

56:25.006 --> 56:27.634
♪ We have to live in the moment ♪

56:27.717 --> 56:30.678
♪ Please smile and accept me ♪

56:30.762 --> 56:33.556
♪ Because we only live once ♪

56:33.640 --> 56:36.434
