♪ In a one-horse open sleigh ♪

57:38.788 --> 57:41.332
♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells ♪

57:41.416 --> 57:42.750
♪ Jingle all the way ♪

57:42.834 --> 57:44.294
[music fades]

57:45.336 --> 57:47.338
[jaunty music playing]

58:16.743 --> 58:18.745
[jaunty music continues]

59:08.419 --> 59:10.296
You gonna die if you don't dance?

59:18.721 --> 59:19.722
Will you?

59:56.426 --> 59:57.594
[music fades]

59:57.677 --> 59:59.679
[indistinct chattering]

01:00:04.934 --> 01:00:05.768
Here.

01:00:05.852 --> 01:00:06.936
Thank you. Cheers.

01:00:25.413 --> 01:00:26.497
[sniffles]

01:00:27.165 --> 01:00:28.291
[sighs]

01:00:28.875 --> 01:00:30.126
Can I ask you something?

01:00:31.878 --> 01:00:32.795
Sure.

01:00:34.589 --> 01:00:39.302
About three years ago,
when you were at the Worlds…

01:00:41.304 --> 01:00:44.641
who was the woman
in the black dress you were dancing with?

01:00:48.102 --> 01:00:49.479
It wasn't Fusako.

01:00:50.188 --> 01:00:52.649
[sniffles] She told Aki it wasn't.

01:00:56.694 --> 01:00:58.529
I'm sure she'd rather forget.

01:00:59.989 --> 01:01:00.907
No.

01:01:02.659 --> 01:01:04.911
Maybe she really can't remember

01:01:05.495 --> 01:01:06.788
what happened.

01:01:12.502 --> 01:01:17.340
What you saw, Mr. Suzuki,
was the World Championships in England.

01:01:18.091 --> 01:01:18.966
[applause]

01:01:19.050 --> 01:01:22.261
[Sugiki] We hadn't been dancing together
for very long.

01:01:26.099 --> 01:01:31.229
The audience really seemed to be fixated
on my new partner.

01:01:39.320 --> 01:01:42.073
["Dancing in the Darkness"
by Suzanne Goodheart playing]

01:02:05.054 --> 01:02:08.015
[Sugiki] That day,
the atmosphere was so tense.

01:02:08.808 --> 01:02:12.228
It happened during
the last dance of the semifinals.

01:02:12.311 --> 01:02:14.355
-We were dancing the quickstep.
-[upbeat music]

01:02:14.439 --> 01:02:17.775
[singer] ♪ Don't let me snooze
I was born to wear these shoes… ♪

01:02:17.859 --> 01:02:19.569
[grunts, groans]

01:02:19.652 --> 01:02:20.820
Are you okay?

01:02:20.903 --> 01:02:22.488
[woman groans]

01:02:23.573 --> 01:02:25.199
[Sugiki] Are you all right?

01:02:25.283 --> 01:02:27.243
[Sugiki] It's not unusual
for dancers to fall,

01:02:27.326 --> 01:02:30.830
but I'd never been associated
with such a bad fall before.

01:02:32.707 --> 01:02:35.251
♪ Wake me up to dance, dance ♪

01:02:35.334 --> 01:02:38.045
-[music fades]
-[Sugiki] That was when it started.

01:02:38.129 --> 01:02:39.630
[Fusako breathing raggedly]

01:02:39.714 --> 01:02:41.424
[melancholy music playing]

01:02:42.258 --> 01:02:44.385
[Sugiki] She began to unravel.

01:02:50.725 --> 01:02:53.686
Years earlier, at a different competition,

01:02:53.770 --> 01:02:56.063
she was dancing with another partner,

01:02:56.147 --> 01:02:58.441
and a similar thing happened.

01:02:59.233 --> 01:03:02.069
She began to suffer
from post-traumatic stress.

01:03:05.740 --> 01:03:07.784
I knew she was going through that,

01:03:09.118 --> 01:03:12.288
but I still got her in that dress
and made her compete in the final.

01:03:17.210 --> 01:03:19.212
[music fades]

01:03:20.463 --> 01:03:22.924
["Fuego" by Gigi Rosa
Dancelife Orchestra playing]

01:03:31.682 --> 01:03:33.851
How did I make her dance, you ask?

01:03:40.149 --> 01:03:43.027
I yelled at and berated her relentlessly.

01:03:43.736 --> 01:03:45.446
["Fuego" continues]

01:03:47.156 --> 01:03:51.035
[Sugiki] Even as her body froze,
her face still reacted to my words,

01:03:51.118 --> 01:03:54.080
and her feet did exactly as I commanded.

01:03:55.289 --> 01:03:57.291
[Sugiki] Your frame, it's loose.

01:03:57.375 --> 01:03:59.001
[crowd clapping]

01:03:59.085 --> 01:04:00.253
[Sugiki] Right side up.

01:04:00.837 --> 01:04:04.090
Keep it. I said keep it.
Your frame is loose.

01:04:04.173 --> 01:04:05.132
It's too loose!

01:04:15.977 --> 01:04:16.978
You're heavy!

01:04:17.061 --> 01:04:19.230
[clapping intensifies]

01:04:19.313 --> 01:04:21.357
Lift your body up. Higher.

01:04:21.858 --> 01:04:22.775
Keep it.

01:04:24.068 --> 01:04:24.986
Keep it.

01:04:26.195 --> 01:04:29.240
[Sugiki] I kept pushing her
until the end of the competition.

01:04:29.323 --> 01:04:31.325
[ethereal pensive music playing]

01:04:36.247 --> 01:04:37.248
And then,

01:04:39.041 --> 01:04:40.418
to my shame,

01:04:42.044 --> 01:04:45.006
I found myself liking her in that state.

01:04:49.176 --> 01:04:50.177
[sighs]

01:04:50.845 --> 01:04:54.515
That's the kind of man I am, I suppose.

01:04:55.016 --> 01:04:55.975
[scoffs]

01:04:56.726 --> 01:04:58.269
Not a gentleman.

01:04:59.353 --> 01:05:01.147
More of a Grim Reaper.

01:05:05.651 --> 01:05:06.736
[Sugiki exhales]

01:05:09.780 --> 01:05:11.699
[Suzuki] Why did I ask him about it?

01:05:18.497 --> 01:05:21.083
I have caused Ms. Yagami so much pain.

01:05:23.502 --> 01:05:25.588
Please keep this between us, okay?

01:05:33.554 --> 01:05:35.514
[Suzuki] Was it a confession I wanted?

01:05:38.267 --> 01:05:40.603
Did I wanna hear him reveal weakness?

01:05:55.451 --> 01:05:56.494
[scoffs]

01:05:58.204 --> 01:05:59.622
Lame, man.

01:06:21.185 --> 01:06:23.187
[train rumbles in distance]

01:06:55.052 --> 01:06:57.054
[poignant piano music playing]

01:07:08.566 --> 01:07:10.568
[distant siren wailing]

01:07:16.657 --> 01:07:18.617
[panting]

01:07:50.733 --> 01:07:52.401
I'll stop if you want.

01:08:16.509 --> 01:08:18.511
[heartfelt music playing]

01:08:24.683 --> 01:08:27.603
[Suzuki] Before I knew it,
my body was moving on its own.

01:08:32.108 --> 01:08:34.193
All I could do was give in to it.

01:08:35.152 --> 01:08:37.279
Surrender to the gods of dance.

01:09:07.726 --> 01:09:09.728
[indistinct chattering]

01:09:20.614 --> 01:09:22.616
[music fades]

01:09:38.007 --> 01:09:40.009
Hang onto that persona of yours.

01:09:44.513 --> 01:09:46.098
You can be the Grim Reaper.

01:09:50.477 --> 01:09:52.479
[gentle piano music playing]

01:09:53.314 --> 01:09:56.483
I'll be the angel who defeats
the Grim Reaper of Blackpool.

01:10:13.792 --> 01:10:15.794
[gentle piano music continues]

01:10:23.135 --> 01:10:24.428
[Suzuki] When I beat you,

01:10:24.929 --> 01:10:28.140
you'll finally be free
of all that suffering.

01:10:32.061 --> 01:10:34.355
[Sugiki] I really admire you, you know.

01:10:35.272 --> 01:10:37.274
[music fades]

01:10:41.320 --> 01:10:43.322
[stirring string music playing]

01:11:23.320 --> 01:11:26.365
[phone buzzing]

01:11:39.461 --> 01:11:41.880
[Sugiki] Let's go overseas together
next time.

01:11:42.840 --> 01:11:46.552
We'll enter as two pairs
in the World Championship at Blackpool.

01:11:50.639 --> 01:11:53.058
I will unveil you to the world.

01:11:54.184 --> 01:11:55.811
It'll be your debut.

01:11:56.562 --> 01:11:58.689
["Double or Nothing"
by Chris Egan playing]

01:12:15.664 --> 01:12:17.666
["Double or Nothing" continues]

01:13:18.268 --> 01:13:19.353
[music ends]

01:13:20.938 --> 01:13:22.022
[Sugiki] How are you?

01:13:22.106 --> 01:13:24.108
[indistinct chattering]

01:13:26.193 --> 01:13:29.029
That's Martha, the president of the WDL.

01:13:29.113 --> 01:13:32.116
And he's a former world champion
who won the Carl Alan Award.

01:13:32.199 --> 01:13:34.827
That's the tournament director,
and that's a big-shot businessman

01:13:34.910 --> 01:13:38.038
who got a medal
for his contributions to the dance world.

01:13:39.832 --> 01:13:41.375
-Hello.
-Hi.

01:13:41.458 --> 01:13:42.876
[Sugiki] Hello, Nino.

01:13:44.169 --> 01:13:46.171
Fabio, good to see you.

01:13:46.255 --> 01:13:48.549
-[man] Fusako. [laughs]
-Hi.

01:13:48.632 --> 01:13:50.551
-[Sugiki] Oh, hi, Catherine.
-Nice to see you.

01:13:50.634 --> 01:13:52.136
Let me introduce you.

01:13:52.219 --> 01:13:54.930
This is our choreographer, Nino,
and our designer, Fabio.

01:13:55.013 --> 01:13:57.850
And this is our hair
and makeup artist, Catherine.

01:13:59.143 --> 01:14:00.894
They're my European tour team.

01:14:00.978 --> 01:14:02.312
Absolutely. Yes.

01:14:02.396 --> 01:14:03.230
Hi, guys.

01:14:03.313 --> 01:14:05.983
So you're the other Shinya? [laughs]

01:14:06.066 --> 01:14:08.986
-Very nice to meet you. A real pleasure.
-Nice to meet you.

01:14:09.069 --> 01:14:11.113
So cute. [chuckles]

01:14:11.196 --> 01:14:12.865
[Nino] And that's Aki, I think.

01:14:12.948 --> 01:14:13.949
[Aki] Yes.

01:14:14.032 --> 01:14:15.576
[Aki, Nino laugh]

01:14:15.659 --> 01:14:17.369
-Hi.
-[Aki] Hi.

01:14:17.453 --> 01:14:19.580
-Very nice to meet you.
-[Nino] Enjoy yourself.

01:14:19.663 --> 01:14:20.831
-[Sugiki] Let's go.
-Thank you.

01:14:20.914 --> 01:14:22.624
-[Fusako] See you soon.
-[Nino] Hi.

01:14:22.708 --> 01:14:24.293
[guest 3] Alberto!

01:14:24.376 --> 01:14:25.586
[guest 4] Alberto!

01:14:25.669 --> 01:14:27.171
[guest 3] So nice to see you!

01:14:27.254 --> 01:14:29.465
That's Alberto, the Latin champion.

01:14:33.635 --> 01:14:35.637
[indistinct chattering]

01:14:37.264 --> 01:14:38.599
Excuse me.

01:14:39.600 --> 01:14:40.684
Shinya.

01:14:45.230 --> 01:14:47.691
He's the ballroom world champion.

01:14:48.358 --> 01:14:49.401
Giulio.

01:14:51.403 --> 01:14:52.779
It's been a while.

01:14:52.863 --> 01:14:54.865
Happy to see you made it.

01:14:56.366 --> 01:14:58.660
[Fusako] And that's Giulio's partner,

01:14:58.744 --> 01:15:01.413
the queen of the dance world, Liana.

01:15:03.457 --> 01:15:06.418
She's also Mr. Sugiki's ex-girlfriend.

01:15:07.586 --> 01:15:09.588
[twangy jaunty music playing]

01:15:11.965 --> 01:15:13.759
[Giulio] I'm here to tell you something.

01:15:16.136 --> 01:15:17.471
Liana and I

01:15:17.554 --> 01:15:20.015
are getting married after the competition.

01:15:23.227 --> 01:15:25.687
Thank you for coming over here to tell me.

01:15:26.313 --> 01:15:27.898
[Giulio] I have your blessing?

01:15:28.774 --> 01:15:29.942
[Sugiki] Of course.

01:15:31.026 --> 01:15:32.528
Congratulations.

01:15:35.447 --> 01:15:37.324
[Suzuki] It's okay, Sugiki.

01:15:37.824 --> 01:15:40.118
I'll make sure you see no one but me.

01:15:44.831 --> 01:15:46.250
Mr. Moretti.

01:15:46.917 --> 01:15:47.876
Nice to meet you.

01:15:47.960 --> 01:15:50.128
My name is Shinya Suzuki,

01:15:50.212 --> 01:15:52.631
and I plan on taking
first place in ballroom

01:15:52.714 --> 01:15:54.967
at the next world championship.

01:15:58.303 --> 01:16:00.138
I've been a fan for a long time.

01:16:00.722 --> 01:16:03.225
Make sure you remember my face.

01:16:18.907 --> 01:16:20.367
[Suzuki] Sugiki, you coming?

01:16:20.909 --> 01:16:21.910
[Sugiki] Yes.

01:16:26.498 --> 01:16:28.500
[twangy jaunty music continues]

01:16:30.335 --> 01:16:31.545
[knocking at door]

01:16:35.090 --> 01:16:36.091
Yeah?

01:16:36.925 --> 01:16:38.927
[distant siren wailing]

01:16:40.470 --> 01:16:41.680
How are you feeling?

01:16:41.763 --> 01:16:43.140
[door closes]

01:16:50.814 --> 01:16:52.608
Here's the schedule for tomorrow.

01:17:00.073 --> 01:17:01.074
[clears throat]

01:17:07.873 --> 01:17:09.708
I want to try more than Latin.

01:17:11.043 --> 01:17:12.836
I wanted to give ballroom a shot.

01:17:14.838 --> 01:17:16.423
Look, we've been over this.

01:17:16.923 --> 01:17:21.094
Keep the fact that you also
do ballroom secret till 10 Dance.

01:17:21.803 --> 01:17:22.638
Hmm?

01:17:25.474 --> 01:17:27.851
You just wanna settle things
with Giulio, right?

01:17:35.025 --> 01:17:36.485
Just do as you're told, okay?

01:17:39.112 --> 01:17:40.989
You like pushing people around.

01:17:43.575 --> 01:17:44.660
Fusako.

01:17:48.080 --> 01:17:48.997
And me?

01:17:54.044 --> 01:17:56.254
[poignant piano music playing]

01:17:57.547 --> 01:17:59.633
Could be you're the fool in the scenario.

01:18:04.429 --> 01:18:06.515
That's why your girl was stolen from you.

01:18:12.896 --> 01:18:14.106
[sighs]

01:18:17.943 --> 01:18:20.320
Just focus on the competition for now.

01:18:24.116 --> 01:18:25.117
Understood?

01:18:39.214 --> 01:18:40.382
[music fades]

01:18:44.803 --> 01:18:46.388
[stirring string music playing]

01:19:14.750 --> 01:19:18.253
I've decided to stop dancing with you…

01:19:22.132 --> 01:19:25.010
and pair up with Giulio instead.

01:19:27.220 --> 01:19:32.058
I need to choose the path
that will make me a champion.

01:19:33.518 --> 01:19:35.145
And if I stay with you,

01:19:36.062 --> 01:19:39.274
I will never become a world champion.

01:19:41.485 --> 01:19:42.736
I'm sure of it.

01:19:48.700 --> 01:19:50.786
[Sugiki] How could she be so sure

01:19:52.704 --> 01:19:54.623
that I could never win?

01:19:59.461 --> 01:20:03.673
If it is true, why do I keep striving?

01:20:04.341 --> 01:20:05.509
[sighs]

01:20:25.904 --> 01:20:30.867
[Martha] Dance is neither
about technique nor stamina.

01:20:32.118 --> 01:20:35.247
Love is what makes it whole.

01:20:41.419 --> 01:20:43.171
Love won't make me win.

01:20:43.255 --> 01:20:45.257
[tender piano music playing]

01:21:02.148 --> 01:21:03.358
[music fades]

01:21:11.408 --> 01:21:12.617
Thank you.

01:21:13.118 --> 01:21:15.579
-Go on in. Upstairs and to the right.
-Straight up the stairs.

01:21:15.662 --> 01:21:16.955
Enjoy yourselves.

01:21:17.622 --> 01:21:18.582
Thank you.

01:21:18.665 --> 01:21:20.125
[indistinct chattering]

01:21:25.088 --> 01:21:27.382
[singer] ♪ Tension rising ♪

01:21:27.465 --> 01:21:28.967
♪ Breath is tight ♪

01:21:29.050 --> 01:21:31.761
♪ You pull me close, I hold you… ♪

01:21:31.845 --> 01:21:34.514
[Suzuki] The World Championships
are just that.

01:21:35.015 --> 01:21:38.268
Over 200 of the world's top pairs
come to compete.

01:21:38.351 --> 01:21:39.185
[cheering]

01:21:39.269 --> 01:21:42.731
One by one, they're eliminated,
like some blood sport.

01:21:43.231 --> 01:21:45.025
Those who survive, the chosen few,

01:21:45.901 --> 01:21:48.361
go at it tooth and nail
for the ultimate titles

01:21:48.945 --> 01:21:51.823
of ballroom and Latin world champions.

01:21:51.907 --> 01:21:53.909
[indistinct chattering]

01:22:11.551 --> 01:22:12.761
You look beautiful.

01:22:12.844 --> 01:22:15.263
-Thanks. You too.
-[Aki chuckles]

01:22:25.482 --> 01:22:28.944
[Fusako] You know, Mr. Sugiki
was seriously thinking of retiring

01:22:29.027 --> 01:22:30.487
not too long ago.

01:22:33.073 --> 01:22:35.241
After he and Liana broke up,

01:22:35.742 --> 01:22:38.328
he couldn't find a partner
who was at his level.

01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:43.166
The ones he did find couldn't keep up
with his strict training.

01:22:45.126 --> 01:22:47.253
The only option he had

01:22:47.879 --> 01:22:50.048
was picking me, the dropout.

01:22:53.134 --> 01:22:55.762
He thinks the only way
he can win the title

01:22:56.596 --> 01:22:59.140
is by pushing himself
to the breaking point.

01:23:02.477 --> 01:23:07.399
I just want… to see
what we can accomplish together.

01:23:09.109 --> 01:23:11.111
[crowd cheering]

01:23:14.739 --> 01:23:16.241
[exhales]

01:23:21.496 --> 01:23:24.124
["The Majestic Tango"
by Dancelife / DJ Sylz playing]

01:23:26.292 --> 01:23:27.669
[crowd clapping]

01:23:28.795 --> 01:23:30.463
[crowd shouting indistinctly]

01:23:31.589 --> 01:23:34.092
[indistinct shouting continues]

01:23:44.978 --> 01:23:46.646
[indistinct shouting continues]

01:23:49.566 --> 01:23:51.693
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:23:53.862 --> 01:23:56.698
[indistinct shouting continues]

01:24:00.035 --> 01:24:01.828
[indistinct shouting continues]

01:24:17.260 --> 01:24:18.511
[music stops]

01:24:18.595 --> 01:24:20.597
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:24:40.116 --> 01:24:44.370
[emcee] Our next competition
is the Professional Latin final.

01:24:44.454 --> 01:24:47.791
Please welcome our finalists to the floor.

01:24:48.500 --> 01:24:50.502
[cheering]

01:24:55.632 --> 01:24:59.552
[emcee] Your first dance, the cha-cha-cha.

01:25:00.053 --> 01:25:03.431
["Sway" by Ross Mitchell
His Band and Singers playing]

01:25:08.728 --> 01:25:10.939
[crowd whistling, cheering]

01:25:22.158 --> 01:25:26.287
[singer] ♪ When marimba rhythms
Start to play ♪

01:25:26.371 --> 01:25:28.331
♪ Dance with me ♪

01:25:28.414 --> 01:25:30.917
♪ Make me sway ♪

01:25:31.543 --> 01:25:35.672
♪ Like a lazy ocean hugs the shore ♪

01:25:35.755 --> 01:25:38.133
♪ Hold me close ♪

01:25:38.216 --> 01:25:40.176
♪ Sway me more ♪

01:25:40.844 --> 01:25:44.639
♪ Like a flower bending in the breeze ♪

01:25:44.722 --> 01:25:47.058
♪ Bend with me ♪

01:25:47.142 --> 01:25:49.853
♪ Sway with ease ♪

01:25:49.936 --> 01:25:53.314
♪ When we dance you have a way with me… ♪

01:25:53.398 --> 01:25:55.608
[Sugiki] The finest dancers

01:25:56.151 --> 01:25:58.528
tell stories with their bodies.

01:25:58.611 --> 01:25:59.487
[music fades]

01:25:59.571 --> 01:26:04.367
They can show the strength
and stoicism of an ancient tree,

01:26:04.868 --> 01:26:07.495
or they can show lightness and air

01:26:07.579 --> 01:26:11.499
as if wings had magically sprouted
from their ankles.

01:26:11.583 --> 01:26:13.585
[tender piano music playing]

01:26:15.503 --> 01:26:17.505
[crowd cheering]

01:26:20.842 --> 01:26:23.428
[man 1] Wow, number 23. Who is that?

01:26:23.511 --> 01:26:25.430
[man 2] His name's
Shinya Suzuki, apparently.

01:26:25.513 --> 01:26:28.516
-[man 1] Shinya Suzuki?
-[man 2] Have you ever heard of this guy?

01:26:28.600 --> 01:26:30.518
[man 3] No, never. Must be an amateur.

01:26:30.602 --> 01:26:32.478
-[man 2] I guess.
-[man 3] He's really good.

01:26:32.979 --> 01:26:34.981
[crowd continues cheering]

01:26:58.963 --> 01:27:04.010
[Sugiki] The story his body was telling
was pure inspiration.

01:27:09.307 --> 01:27:10.642
Suddenly,

01:27:11.684 --> 01:27:14.062
I could see a way forward.

01:27:22.070 --> 01:27:23.988
["Sway" resumes]

01:27:24.072 --> 01:27:28.117
♪ I can hear the sound of violins ♪

01:27:28.201 --> 01:27:29.827
♪ Long before ♪

01:27:29.911 --> 01:27:32.413
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:27:35.959 --> 01:27:39.003
[woman 3] Oh God, I didn't know
anyone could dance like that.

01:27:39.087 --> 01:27:41.339
[man 5] Who is that?
Is that the Japanese guy?

01:27:41.422 --> 01:27:42.340
Wow.

01:27:42.423 --> 01:27:45.969
[man 6] This is not a dance competition.
It's like a brawl.

01:27:46.052 --> 01:27:50.848
The judge will likely take marks off,
but it sure is captivating.

01:27:50.932 --> 01:27:52.934
[cheering, clapping continues]

01:28:12.120 --> 01:28:17.500
[emcee] We come now to the result
of the 73rd World Championship,

01:28:17.583 --> 01:28:19.752
ballroom division.

01:28:20.253 --> 01:28:22.964
Into first place,

01:28:23.047 --> 01:28:26.801
Giulio Moretti and Liana Javalanka.

01:28:28.177 --> 01:28:30.179
[crowd cheering, clapping continues]

01:28:37.729 --> 01:28:41.107
[emcee] Into second place,

01:28:41.190 --> 01:28:44.736
Shinya Sugiki and Fusako Yagami.

01:28:44.819 --> 01:28:47.030
[crowd cheering, clapping continues]

01:28:54.120 --> 01:28:58.875
Third, Dusan Novak and Valeria Orlova.

01:29:00.460 --> 01:29:02.628
[Nino] I remember
when he and Liana danced together

01:29:02.712 --> 01:29:04.547
before he paired up with Fusako.

01:29:04.630 --> 01:29:09.010
Their tango was so…
[inhales sharply] …passionate.

01:29:09.093 --> 01:29:15.516
Uh, I mean, it was obvious
that Shinya was crazy about Liana.

01:29:16.601 --> 01:29:19.896
But when he proposed to her,
something got in the way.

01:29:19.979 --> 01:29:21.230
[Fabio] So I hear.

01:29:21.314 --> 01:29:24.650
Giulio and Shinya's attack
is very similar.

01:29:24.734 --> 01:29:26.694
Their ability is evenly matched,

01:29:26.778 --> 01:29:31.115
or perhaps maybe there's just
the narrowest of margins between them.

01:29:31.199 --> 01:29:34.160
But the one who gets to stand
at the top of the podium is who?

01:29:34.243 --> 01:29:35.411
-Giulio.
-[Nino] Giulio.

01:29:35.495 --> 01:29:38.581
[Fabio] Shinya doesn't have what it takes
to overcome that slight margin.

01:29:38.664 --> 01:29:41.501
-I'm sorry, Nino.
-No. I don't agree, Fabio. No, no, no.

01:29:41.584 --> 01:29:45.421
Everyone is here to see
his obsessive determination.

01:29:45.505 --> 01:29:46.339
[Fabio] I know.

01:29:46.422 --> 01:29:49.425
[Nino] And everyone comes here
to see him valiantly struggle…

01:29:49.509 --> 01:29:50.593
[sighs]

01:29:50.676 --> 01:29:52.887
…just to end up losing again.

01:29:52.970 --> 01:29:53.930
[Fabio] Yes.

01:29:54.013 --> 01:29:57.058
[Nino] The only person here
who thinks he has a chance of winning

01:29:57.141 --> 01:29:59.852
is probably Shinya himself.

01:30:02.271 --> 01:30:04.065
What the hell are you saying?

01:30:04.649 --> 01:30:06.442
-Excuse me?
-Don't just say that.

01:30:06.526 --> 01:30:08.403
Do something about it!

01:30:08.486 --> 01:30:10.279
That "slight margin" you mentioned,

01:30:10.363 --> 01:30:13.366
you mean Sugiki's
actually a better dancer, right?

01:30:14.409 --> 01:30:18.121
-So help him win!
-Easy, calm down. Come on, Shinya, please.

01:30:18.204 --> 01:30:20.456
You guys have the power to do that,
don't you?

01:30:20.540 --> 01:30:21.457
No, I… I don't know.

01:30:21.541 --> 01:30:23.709
-I'm telling you, let him fucking win!
-Hey. Whoa, whoa!

01:30:23.793 --> 01:30:25.753
-[Fabio] Calm down.
-[Nino] Hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:30:25.837 --> 01:30:26.963
-[Fabio] Easy.
-[Nino] Sorry…

01:30:27.046 --> 01:30:28.423
-That's bullshit!
-[Nino] I'm sorry.

01:30:28.506 --> 01:30:32.718
-But there's nothing we can do.
-I… I'm so sorry. So sorry.

01:30:32.802 --> 01:30:34.887
[emcee] Ladies and gentlemen,

01:30:34.971 --> 01:30:39.308
next we have a very special honor dance.

01:30:39.392 --> 01:30:41.936
Please welcome to the floor

01:30:42.019 --> 01:30:44.689
Liana and Shinya.

01:30:45.189 --> 01:30:47.191
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:30:50.027 --> 01:30:51.779
-[man 7] Swapping partners?
-[man 8] A switch!

01:30:51.863 --> 01:30:55.366
-Shinya and Liana? That's fantastic!
-[man 7] That's fantastic!

01:31:06.502 --> 01:31:08.504
[crowd cheering]

01:31:10.339 --> 01:31:12.383
-[spectator 1] Shinya!
-[spectator 2] Shinya!

01:31:15.595 --> 01:31:17.305
[clapping subsides]

01:31:22.643 --> 01:31:24.395
["Anticipation" by Cantaluna playing]

01:31:39.660 --> 01:31:41.662
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:31:48.211 --> 01:31:50.963
[Fabio] This is a total charade,
but look at him.

01:31:51.047 --> 01:31:51.881
[Nino] Mm.

01:31:51.964 --> 01:31:54.926
Sugiki plays the part
of the perfect gentleman.

01:31:55.843 --> 01:31:58.763
-You know, even I wanna be like him.
-[Nino] I know what you mean.

01:31:58.846 --> 01:32:02.225
[Fabio] He's the ideal lover
that everyone wants to be.

01:32:02.308 --> 01:32:04.477
[Nino] So true. So true.

01:32:12.026 --> 01:32:14.028
[clapping continues]

01:32:31.921 --> 01:32:33.923
[crowd cheering]

01:32:57.905 --> 01:33:00.199
[cheering]

01:33:23.472 --> 01:33:24.682
[music fades]

01:33:24.765 --> 01:33:27.602
[poignant music playing]

01:33:34.984 --> 01:33:36.986
[poignant music continues]

01:34:02.345 --> 01:34:03.721
[knocking at door]

01:34:12.355 --> 01:34:13.981
[knocking at door]

01:34:28.621 --> 01:34:30.623
[music fades]

01:34:36.337 --> 01:34:38.214
[Sugiki] That was a wonderful debut.

01:34:40.633 --> 01:34:42.134
Where is Ms. Tajima?

01:34:43.803 --> 01:34:46.639
-[Suzuki] I don't know.
-[Sugiki] I see.

01:34:52.436 --> 01:34:53.813
[Suzuki sighs]

01:34:56.315 --> 01:34:57.525
[Suzuki sniffles]

01:34:59.193 --> 01:35:00.611
[Suzuki sighs]

01:35:06.867 --> 01:35:08.452
Didn't that bug you today?

01:35:10.579 --> 01:35:11.497
Ah.

01:35:12.123 --> 01:35:13.499
No, not at all.

01:35:14.250 --> 01:35:16.293
Liana and I were done a long time ago.

01:35:17.920 --> 01:35:19.463
You haven't moved on though.

01:35:24.427 --> 01:35:26.929
-[liquid pouring]
-I can't stand that kinda thing.

01:35:29.265 --> 01:35:30.599
Being deceived.

01:35:33.102 --> 01:35:34.437
Betrayed.

01:35:38.607 --> 01:35:40.067
I can't forgive that.

01:35:51.662 --> 01:35:55.040
So you think I'm still in love with Liana?

01:35:57.001 --> 01:35:59.545
That I've never even looked
at another woman?

01:36:00.463 --> 01:36:03.632
That I've remained totally devoted to her?

01:36:05.885 --> 01:36:07.303
Is that what you saw?

01:36:09.638 --> 01:36:10.556
Well?

01:36:11.932 --> 01:36:13.100
[Sugiki scoffs]

01:36:13.184 --> 01:36:15.644
If the audience saw a reunion
between two lovers,

01:36:15.728 --> 01:36:17.980
then tonight's show was a success.

01:36:19.607 --> 01:36:22.818
No one was watching Giulio's performance
after that, were they?

01:36:24.320 --> 01:36:25.404
[Suzuki tuts]

01:36:26.197 --> 01:36:27.448
What do you mean?

01:36:30.201 --> 01:36:31.243
What?

01:36:36.540 --> 01:36:38.417
What the hell are you saying?

01:36:41.378 --> 01:36:43.088
You're really okay with it?

01:36:48.511 --> 01:36:50.596
I'm asking if that's really good enough…

01:36:50.679 --> 01:36:51.889
-[glass shatters]
-…for you!

01:37:04.276 --> 01:37:07.363
You said you wouldn't settle
for anything but first place.

01:37:10.950 --> 01:37:12.159
[exhales sharply]

01:37:22.837 --> 01:37:23.879
[moans]

01:37:52.366 --> 01:37:53.450
[exhales sharply]

01:37:53.534 --> 01:37:55.578
[breathing heavily]

01:38:01.333 --> 01:38:02.501
[Suzuki] What's wrong?

01:38:04.712 --> 01:38:05.796
What is it?

01:38:12.136 --> 01:38:13.512
[breathing heavily]

01:38:14.179 --> 01:38:15.180
[groans]

01:38:16.807 --> 01:38:17.933
[grunts]

01:38:20.185 --> 01:38:22.021
[gasping]

01:38:23.272 --> 01:38:24.940
[Suzuki grunts, breathes heavily]

01:38:36.869 --> 01:38:38.954
[Sugiki] I can't be with you anymore.

01:38:40.039 --> 01:38:42.583
If we go any further, it could destroy me.

01:38:43.167 --> 01:38:45.377
[Suzuki breathing heavily]

01:38:46.253 --> 01:38:47.463
What the fuck?

01:38:50.549 --> 01:38:53.969
-That's not it.
-No, stop! You're my enemy now.

01:38:57.723 --> 01:38:59.308
That's not true.

01:39:29.713 --> 01:39:31.715
[poignant piano music playing]

01:39:53.195 --> 01:39:54.446
In the end…

01:40:03.122 --> 01:40:05.249
you and I can never become one.

01:40:24.852 --> 01:40:26.145
[door opens]

01:40:30.733 --> 01:40:31.984
[door closes]

01:40:47.291 --> 01:40:48.625
[music fades]

01:40:49.793 --> 01:40:50.878
[dog barks]

01:40:53.630 --> 01:40:55.632
[melancholy music playing]

01:41:18.489 --> 01:41:19.448
Shit.

01:41:25.245 --> 01:41:26.288
[groans]

01:41:45.891 --> 01:41:47.184
[sniffles]

01:42:04.201 --> 01:42:05.369
[music fades]

01:42:09.081 --> 01:42:11.083
[vehicle approaching]

01:42:20.384 --> 01:42:22.386
[car door opens, closes]

01:42:32.855 --> 01:42:33.814
Shinya.

01:43:08.223 --> 01:43:09.141
Shinya.

01:43:13.937 --> 01:43:15.939
[breathes deeply]

01:43:16.648 --> 01:43:18.025
I realized something.

01:43:22.029 --> 01:43:23.947
I think I can do more for you.

01:43:29.578 --> 01:43:31.538
We can do more. I just know it.

01:43:36.210 --> 01:43:37.920
And even if it's just you…

01:43:39.379 --> 01:43:40.380
[sniffles]

01:43:41.131 --> 01:43:42.799
…you can go far!

01:43:44.760 --> 01:43:46.720
You could go as far as you want.

01:43:54.478 --> 01:43:55.604
[Aki sniffles]

01:44:04.154 --> 01:44:05.197
[sniffles]

01:44:13.288 --> 01:44:14.289
Let's go.

01:44:15.290 --> 01:44:16.291
[Aki] Huh?

01:44:17.918 --> 01:44:18.752
What?

01:44:19.253 --> 01:44:21.255
[gentle piano music playing]

01:44:25.133 --> 01:44:27.052
[man] The yellow is very nice.

01:44:27.135 --> 01:44:28.720
[Aki] Isn't is amazing?

01:44:28.804 --> 01:44:31.098
[man] This and…

01:44:31.181 --> 01:44:32.391
[Aki] Ah!

01:44:32.474 --> 01:44:34.268
[man] Hmm, no, no, no.

01:44:34.935 --> 01:44:35.769
Red.

01:44:35.852 --> 01:44:37.562
I wanna see you in red.

01:44:39.273 --> 01:44:42.651
-[Suzuki] So you're gonna go with that?
-[Aki] Yeah. Isn't it cool?

01:44:44.152 --> 01:44:45.487
[chuckles]

01:44:45.570 --> 01:44:49.074
Now, do we want it parted to this side?
Or to that side?

01:44:49.157 --> 01:44:51.451
[man] Neater and more polished.

01:44:57.916 --> 01:45:00.877
[man 2] So I want to show you
the beginning of Alemana.

01:45:00.961 --> 01:45:03.338
We're going to do four to six.

01:45:03.422 --> 01:45:05.549
Let's do sliding doors.
Just the beginning.

01:45:06.216 --> 01:45:08.218
[uplifting music playing]

01:45:46.006 --> 01:45:47.090
[groans]

01:46:29.758 --> 01:46:31.760
[music subsides]

01:46:34.262 --> 01:46:36.264
[gentle piano music playing]

01:46:50.946 --> 01:46:52.948
[train rumbles in distance]

01:47:30.152 --> 01:47:32.779
["River Flows in You" playing]

01:47:32.863 --> 01:47:34.865
[applause]

01:47:51.798 --> 01:47:53.967
[man] This is the first time
a dance competition in Japan

01:47:54.050 --> 01:47:56.011
has gotten this much media attention,
isn't it?

01:47:56.094 --> 01:47:57.554
[man 2] Yeah, seems so.

01:47:58.680 --> 01:48:01.808
It's too bad Giulio and Alberto
aren't here though.

01:48:01.892 --> 01:48:04.769
They backed out.
Said they had a show to do.

01:48:05.687 --> 01:48:08.523
I say first place will go to Shinya.

01:48:09.649 --> 01:48:11.693
He'll place third at best.

01:48:11.776 --> 01:48:12.652
What?

01:48:13.820 --> 01:48:16.323
Well, why do you think the federation
put up the money

01:48:16.406 --> 01:48:18.950
and brought in so many foreign dancers?

01:48:19.034 --> 01:48:21.745
They're going to want
some kind of payback, you know?

01:48:24.122 --> 01:48:26.791
That's the dance world for ya, huh?

01:48:27.584 --> 01:48:28.960
[energetic samba music playing]

01:48:34.466 --> 01:48:36.468
[melodic waltz music playing]

01:48:55.987 --> 01:48:58.907
Mr. Sugiki is the guest, right?

01:49:01.785 --> 01:49:03.411
So, he's here.

01:49:07.916 --> 01:49:09.834
I won't ever see him again

01:49:10.377 --> 01:49:12.170
outside of competition.

01:49:12.837 --> 01:49:14.005
[Suzuki groans]

01:49:15.924 --> 01:49:18.009
When I saw him in Blackpool, it…

01:49:20.303 --> 01:49:22.013
it wasn't just dancing.

01:49:23.807 --> 01:49:26.184
The crowd and the other dancers…

01:49:28.311 --> 01:49:29.813
they were blown away by it.

01:49:32.857 --> 01:49:34.776
[distant cheering, clapping]

01:49:34.859 --> 01:49:37.529
I wanna move the audience like that
every time.

01:49:50.000 --> 01:49:52.127
[man 3] Five-minute call
for the finalists!

01:49:53.461 --> 01:49:55.964
Can I get everyone
to come together, please?

01:49:57.507 --> 01:49:59.801
All finalists, please come this way.

01:50:12.897 --> 01:50:14.649
[distant clapping]

01:50:16.443 --> 01:50:21.948
[emcee] The next event will be
the Professional Latin American final.

01:50:22.032 --> 01:50:24.034
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:50:44.012 --> 01:50:46.431
So close, and yet so far.

01:50:58.318 --> 01:51:00.320
["Gold Top" by Chris Egan playing]

01:51:05.742 --> 01:51:07.744
[crowd cheering]

01:51:20.715 --> 01:51:22.717
[cheering continues]

01:51:35.438 --> 01:51:40.485
[Martha] Dance is neither
about technique nor stamina.

01:51:44.239 --> 01:51:46.950
Love is what makes it whole.

01:51:47.033 --> 01:51:48.576
[cheering fades]

01:51:51.830 --> 01:51:53.957
And once again,

01:51:54.040 --> 01:52:01.005
here are the 2026 Asian Cup
ballroom champions,

01:52:01.089 --> 01:52:06.511
Leonardo Fontana and Sofia Rossi!

01:52:06.594 --> 01:52:08.888
[crowd cheering]

01:52:08.972 --> 01:52:14.436
[emcee] And the 2026
Asian Cup Latin champions,

01:52:14.519 --> 01:52:19.733
Alessandro Leon and Annamaria Valentini!

01:52:19.816 --> 01:52:22.277
[crowd cheering]

01:52:22.360 --> 01:52:27.282
[emcee] Please give our champions
another big round of applause.

01:52:27.365 --> 01:52:29.367
[crowd cheering]

01:52:30.952 --> 01:52:35.331
[emcee] They will be back later
to perform an honor dance for us.

01:52:35.415 --> 01:52:40.587
And now, we have a demonstration
by our special guests,

01:52:41.212 --> 01:52:44.382
the UK ballroom champions,

01:52:44.466 --> 01:52:50.472
Shinya Sugiki and Fusako Yagami.

01:52:51.639 --> 01:52:53.641
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:53:19.501 --> 01:53:21.419
[cheering, clapping subsides]

01:53:21.503 --> 01:53:23.505
[indistinct chattering]

01:53:40.939 --> 01:53:42.941
[crowd murmuring]

01:53:59.707 --> 01:54:01.376
Will you do me the honor?

01:54:43.501 --> 01:54:45.503
[crowd murmuring]

01:55:18.536 --> 01:55:20.538
["Lasso the Moon" playing]

01:55:34.969 --> 01:55:38.681
♪ If I were a carpenter ♪

01:55:38.765 --> 01:55:42.936
♪ I'd build a world of love ♪

01:55:43.019 --> 01:55:46.856
♪ Where we would always be ♪

01:55:46.940 --> 01:55:51.486
♪ Together ♪

01:55:51.569 --> 01:55:55.406
♪ If I were the captain of… ♪

01:55:55.490 --> 01:55:58.284
[emcee] The first dance is the waltz.

01:55:59.869 --> 01:56:02.914
A beautiful slow waltz.

01:56:07.961 --> 01:56:10.088
["Tango Brujo" playing]

01:56:13.591 --> 01:56:15.301
[crowd clapping]

01:56:16.010 --> 01:56:17.762
[emcee] The tango.

01:56:19.430 --> 01:56:21.808
An exciting tango!

01:56:29.315 --> 01:56:31.734
♪ Only in New York ♪

01:56:33.194 --> 01:56:35.905
♪ On Fifth Avenue… ♪

01:56:35.989 --> 01:56:38.157
[emcee] The slow foxtrot.

01:56:38.866 --> 01:56:41.369
An elegant slow foxtrot.

01:56:41.452 --> 01:56:43.454
♪ Dripping with pearls ♪

01:56:43.538 --> 01:56:45.540
♪ Oh, what a view… ♪

01:56:47.417 --> 01:56:51.421
♪ The subway crawls
From the street with walls ♪

01:56:51.504 --> 01:56:54.924
♪ To Harlem, where music plays ♪

01:56:55.842 --> 01:56:58.761
["Takeoff" by Ballroom Orchestra
and Singers ft. Gigi Rosa]

01:56:59.595 --> 01:57:02.640
♪ We go, take off, take off
Runway clear… ♪

01:57:02.724 --> 01:57:05.059
♪ Click, step, ready, shoot that beer ♪

01:57:05.143 --> 01:57:06.644
♪ Slide to the side… ♪

01:57:06.728 --> 01:57:08.229
[emcee] The quick step!

01:57:09.647 --> 01:57:12.567
The fourth dance is the quick step!

01:57:13.985 --> 01:57:15.069
♪ Let's go ♪

01:57:15.153 --> 01:57:17.155
[crowd cheering]

01:57:22.201 --> 01:57:26.539
♪ When marimba rhythms start to play ♪

01:57:26.622 --> 01:57:27.665
♪ Dance with me ♪

01:57:27.749 --> 01:57:29.459
[emcee] The cha-cha-cha.

01:57:30.626 --> 01:57:33.463
Feel the rhythm of the cha-cha-cha.

01:57:33.546 --> 01:57:35.673
♪ Hugs the shore ♪

01:57:35.757 --> 01:57:37.759
♪ Hold me close ♪

01:57:37.842 --> 01:57:39.510
♪ Sway me more ♪

01:57:39.594 --> 01:57:41.345
[crowd cheering]

01:57:41.429 --> 01:57:44.932
["Bailando en Las Calles de Rio"
by Gigi Rosa / Dancelife Orchestra]

01:57:46.142 --> 01:57:47.226
[emcee] The samba!

01:58:01.449 --> 01:58:04.202
Shake your body to the samba!

01:58:04.285 --> 01:58:06.245
[crowd cheering, clapping]

01:58:08.414 --> 01:58:11.834
["Sin Tu Amor" by Ballroom Orchestra
and Singers ft. Gigi Rosa]

01:58:15.588 --> 01:58:17.048
[emcee] The rumba.

01:58:17.548 --> 01:58:21.469
A dance for love, the rumba.

01:58:40.196 --> 01:58:42.198
["España Cañí" playing]

01:58:45.409 --> 01:58:47.703
[emcee] The paso doble.

01:58:48.371 --> 01:58:50.206
Feel the passion!

01:58:50.289 --> 01:58:52.500
The paso doble.

01:58:52.583 --> 01:58:54.836
[crowd rhythmically clapping]

01:59:05.888 --> 01:59:09.016
["Gold Top" by Chris Egan playing]

01:59:09.684 --> 01:59:11.269
[emcee] The jive!

01:59:12.270 --> 01:59:13.938
Let's swing together.

01:59:14.021 --> 01:59:16.440
Here comes the jive!

01:59:31.455 --> 01:59:33.457
[crowd cheering]

01:59:42.091 --> 01:59:44.093
["Minute Waltz" playing]

01:59:50.683 --> 01:59:53.311
[emcee] The Viennese waltz.

01:59:54.145 --> 01:59:58.482
The last dance is the Viennese waltz.

02:00:37.730 --> 02:00:39.607
I'll see you at the 10 Dance.

02:01:43.796 --> 02:01:46.299
-[emcee] 10 Dance.
-[music ends]

02:01:48.301 --> 02:01:50.303
[jaunty music playing]

02:04:06.188 --> 02:04:07.940
[music fades]

02:04:09.483 --> 02:04:11.485
[stirring melodic music playing]

02:04:55.988 --> 02:04:57.990
[music fades]

02:05:00.326 --> 02:05:02.328
[heartfelt string music playing]

02:06:30.833 --> 02:06:32.960
[music fades]
